column1: Municipal and City Level Small Area Poverty Estimates; 2006, 2009 and 2012

Source: Philippine Statistics Authority, through a national government funded project on the generation of the 2012 small area estimates on poverty. Please note that the 2009 small area estimates of poverty were generated through funding assistance from the Government of the Philippines, World Bank and the Australian Government.
Note:     The standard deviation of an estimate can be derived by multiplying the poverty incidence and coefficient of variation then divide by 100.
*Estimates are reliable if the coefficient of variation is at most 20 %
